Police have arrested suspected killer of Nasarawa State chairman of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Chief Philip Tatari Shekwo. Governor Abdullahi Sule confirmed the arrest at a job fair yesterday in Lafia. The suspect, Mohammed Usman, according to the governor, is a notorious bandit and kidnapper. He was picked by security operatives at Asakio, Lafia East Local Council, and has reportedly confessed to the crime. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .